So why are fast ions
so important in the plasma external

177
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:10,400
and self-heating process?

178
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:13,223
I remind that here in this sketch,

179
00:10:13,336 --> 00:10:17,750
we of course here have the plasma 
in which inject power from outside

180
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:20,507
and we have reactions
that produce α-particles

181
00:10:20,507 --> 00:10:25,039
which carry about 20% of the energy
which must be kept in the plasma.

182
00:10:25,112 --> 00:10:27,503
And the neutrons
that come out of the plasma

183
00:10:27,503 --> 00:10:29,070
with about 80% of energy.

184
00:10:29,070 --> 00:10:32,250
So the loop works as follows:
we heat the ions, they fuse,

185
00:10:32,457 --> 00:10:37,988
they produce α-particles and therefore
a significant α-particles power.

186
00:10:38,218 --> 00:10:44,260
Which will therefore, subsequently,
be given to the electrons

187
00:10:44,260 --> 00:10:45,767
via collisional process.

188
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:50,743
As we have seen when we discussed
the neutral beam injection heating method,

189
00:10:51,374 --> 00:10:56,699
if the energy of the fast particles
is very large,

190
00:10:56,867 --> 00:11:01,573
the collisional process will first give
this energy to the electrons

191
00:11:01,573 --> 00:11:02,766
rather than to the ions.

192
00:11:02,766 --> 00:11:07,276
This is why I have represented this loop
as the collisional processes giving energy

193
00:11:07,276 --> 00:11:08,751
from the α's to the electrons,

194
00:11:08,827 --> 00:11:12,159
which in turn have to
thermalize on the ions.

195
00:11:12,322 --> 00:11:15,877
It will be sort of indirect heating
of the ions via the electrons.

196
00:11:16,317 --> 00:11:19,045
This is if we count on
the α-particle heating,

197
00:11:19,045 --> 00:11:23,395
but similarly we have the same situation
for the fast ions

198
00:11:23,395 --> 00:11:27,209
if we count on ICRH or NBI,
because in those cases

199
00:11:27,209 --> 00:11:30,342
you produce fast ions
they will then again,

200
00:11:30,342 --> 00:11:36,501
depending on the energy, giving it
to the electrons or directly to the ions.

201
00:11:36,603 --> 00:11:40,215
So fast ions are very important 
in the process of heating a plasma

202
00:11:40,255 --> 00:11:43,760
both from external sources, 
at least for ICRH or NBI,

