420
00:24:46,763 --> 00:24:50,336
in the core performance
of the fusion reactor.

421
00:24:50,899 --> 00:24:53,766
The second example is even 
more ubiquitous,

422
00:24:53,810 --> 00:24:55,905
it is the so-called <i>sawtooth</i> instability.

423
00:24:56,147 --> 00:25:00,627
This is an instability
that leads to a series of sudden collapses

424
00:25:00,627 --> 00:25:02,475
of energy and particles in the core,

425
00:25:03,309 --> 00:25:05,798
represented by this shape.

426
00:25:05,880 --> 00:25:08,179
And that’s why we refer to it
as a sawtooth.

427
00:25:08,702 --> 00:25:11,981
In this case, I represented
the temperature as a function of time.

428
00:25:12,021 --> 00:25:16,778
When the collapse occurs, 
in fact there is a local breaking

429
00:25:16,778 --> 00:25:20,221
of the magnetic structure, just like what
happens in the geomagnetic tail.

430
00:25:20,257 --> 00:25:23,675
in a phenomenon you have seen 
in other lectures of this course,

431
00:25:23,675 --> 00:25:25,308
called <i>magnetic reconnection</i>.

432
00:25:26,989 --> 00:25:31,427
This is linked to an MHD 
instability of the kink type,

433
00:25:32,180 --> 00:25:34,675
which we have also illustrated to you
in previous lectures.

434
00:25:34,895 --> 00:25:37,736
But the frequency is even smaller
than the precession frequency

435
00:25:37,736 --> 00:25:38,602
for the fast ions,

436
00:25:38,602 --> 00:25:41,784
so this is not really 
a resonant and driven instability

437
00:25:41,789 --> 00:25:44,632
in the sense of a wave particle resonance
with the fast ions,

438
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:48,491
nevertheless, the fast ions 
are affected by the instability

439
00:25:48,491 --> 00:25:53,138
because they are ejected together
with the parts of the core plasma.

440
00:25:54,098 --> 00:25:57,123
This phenomenon, in fact, 
is being illustrated as we speak

441
00:25:57,123 --> 00:26:00,891
on the little movie on the right

442
00:26:00,891 --> 00:26:05,260
which shows the X-ray 
emissivity evolution in the TCV tokamak

443
00:26:05,260 --> 00:26:07,210
over a sawtooth cycle.

444
00:26:07,836 --> 00:26:12,676
This sudden collapses
not only are they a problem,

445
00:26:12,676 --> 00:26:17,992
because they kick out the fast ions 
and the core of the plasma

446
00:26:17,992 --> 00:26:20,253
or they re-distribute
the central region of the plasma,

447
00:26:20,253 --> 00:26:25,336
but also they can trigger
secondary instabilities.

448
00:26:27,098 --> 00:26:30,798
Because the fast ions influence
the period of the sawteeth,

449
00:26:31,297 --> 00:26:34,264
which in turn determines
the strength of the collapse,

450
00:26:34,264 --> 00:26:37,093
the fast ions can be used to control
these modes and therefore,

451
00:26:37,093 --> 00:26:39,101
to control the secondary instabilities.

452
00:26:39,218 --> 00:26:42,419
And this is really a very 
active line of research.

453
00:26:43,111 --> 00:26:47,726
Another possible channel for losing
